The question mark character (?) is used to specify a match condition. In this case, the pattern is asking whether there exists a single character before it that matches (traditionally ^ for line, .= for character, etc are used prepend to a token to match at the start of the string or the character set respectively). Since 'a' is the first character, there is no previous character for it to match.
